         <div xml:id="main">
            <head type="incipit">
               <supplied reason="XTF-compatibility">24/8/94 ¶  ¶ Best thanks for your kind letter, dear Dr Broom, and the information, which it conveyed. The deep ravines at the Upper Macleay-River ¶  are as yet imperfectly explored for their vegetatio...</supplied>
            </head>
            <p rend="number" xml:lang="en">94.08.24a</p>
            <p rend="correspondent" xml:lang="en">To Robert Broom</p>
            <p rend="location" xml:lang="en">MS 9036, National Library of Australia, Canberra.</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; text-align: end; "
               xml:lang="en">24/8/94</p>
            <space dim="vertical" unit="lines" quantity="1"/>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Best thanks for your kind letter, dear Dr Broom, and the information, which it conveyed. The deep ravines at the Upper Macleay-River<note xml:id="ftn1" type="footnote" n="1">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="">NSW.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> are as yet imperfectly explored for their vegetation; indeed some of them have never been thus far examined. Perhaps Settlers near these abysses, could be induced to let youths<note xml:id="ftn2" type="footnote" n="2">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">children <seg style="font-style: italic; ">deleted.</seg>
                  </p>
               </note> of theirs collect all sorts of plants in these deep vallied, and bring a couple of handkerchiefs full to you for selecting specimens therefrom. This could probably be done at a trifling expense, and it would involve little trouble to yourself. Doubtless novelties exist yet in these exist yet in these<note xml:id="ftn3" type="footnote" n="3">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">
                     <seg style="font-style: italic; ">sic</seg> – line repeated.</p>
               </note> gorges, for the discovery of which you would get full credit.</p>
            <p rend="letter"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>It is very kind of you to offer me an extraprint of your important abstract treatise,<note xml:id="ftn4" type="footnote" n="4">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">Broom (1894)?</p>
               </note> as I can utilize it in my litterary interchanges. Among the fine medical periodicals, which I get regularly, is also the Sydney Medical Gazette<note xml:id="ftn5" type="footnote" n="5">
                  <p rend="Footnote"
                     style="font-family: Geneva; margin-left: 0.3335in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: -0.3335in; font-size: 9pt; "
                     xml:lang="en">i.e. <seg style="font-style: italic; ">Australasian medical gazette</seg> published in Sydney.</p>
               </note>
            </p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">Most regardfully your</p>
            <p rend="valediction"
               style="font-family: Geneva; font-size: 12pt; margin-left: 1.75in; margin-right: 0in; text-indent: 0in; "
               xml:lang="en">
               <space dim="horizontal" extent="tab"/>Ferd von Mueller</p>
         </div>
      </body>
